{
  "texts": [
    "The background gradient also shows the areas of decision of the SVM model, different color tones representing the confidence level for each class.",
    "The solid line placed in the middle of the two areas is the decision plane that is determined by SVM that partitions the feature space into anomaly and normal zones.",
    "There is also an illustration of the SVM in distinguishing the classes whose joint map shows that there is a degree of misclassification in some parts of the map.",
    "This particular decision boundary does a good job of showing how the model works and makes decisions when sorting through the provided set.",
    "Random Forest is an ensemble learning method that combines multiple decision trees to improve classification accuracy."
  ]
}